1
01:00:00,566 --> 01:00:02,733
<b>The Israel-Palestinian conflict.</b>

2
01:00:04,066 --> 01:00:06,633
<b>It is so complex and emotionally charged</b>

3
01:00:06,633 --> 01:00:08,933
<b>that most of us try to avoid it.</b>

4
01:00:09,233 --> 01:00:11,933
<b>But if you're into history, it's a puzzle</b>

5
01:00:11,933 --> 01:00:13,099
<b>that's hard to resist.</b>

6
01:00:13,400 --> 01:00:16,433
<b>A story of empires, nationalism and</b>

7
01:00:16,433 --> 01:00:18,666
<b>ancient claims that seem to</b>

8
01:00:18,666 --> 01:00:20,633
<b>cry out for historical answer.</b>

9
01:00:21,033 --> 01:00:23,599
<b>The problem is, even the most dedicated</b>

10
01:00:23,599 --> 01:00:25,933
<b>students of history often build their</b>

11
01:00:25,933 --> 01:00:27,766
<b>understanding on a foundation of myths.</b>

12
01:00:27,833 --> 01:00:31,199
<b>Powerful, persuasive and historically</b>

13
01:00:31,199 --> 01:00:33,533
<b>inaccurate stories that shape everything</b>

14
01:00:33,533 --> 01:00:35,099
<b>that we think that we know.</b>

15
01:00:35,433 --> 01:00:37,433
<b>What if I told you that the common belief</b>

16
01:00:37,433 --> 01:00:40,266
<b>that this is an ancient religious war,</b>

17
01:00:40,500 --> 01:00:42,833
<b>raging for millennia between Jews and</b>

18
01:00:42,833 --> 01:00:45,033
<b>Muslims, is fundamentally wrong?</b>

19
01:00:45,300 --> 01:00:47,066
<b>That the historical record actually</b>

20
01:00:47,066 --> 01:00:50,866
<b>points towards a much more recent and</b>

21
01:00:50,866 --> 01:00:52,866
<b>totally different origin story.</b>

22
01:00:53,433 --> 01:00:55,099
<b>That's just one of the foundational myths</b>

23
01:00:55,099 --> 01:00:55,766
<b>that we're going to tackle.</b>

24
01:00:56,800 --> 01:00:58,933
<b>So, let's get into the five most</b>

25
01:00:58,933 --> 01:01:01,066
<b>significant myths that you probably think</b>

26
01:01:01,066 --> 01:01:03,000
<b>are true, and see why the historical</b>

27
01:01:03,000 --> 01:01:04,533
<b>record proves them false.</b>

28
01:01:05,166 --> 01:01:08,566
<b>Myth 1. An ancient religious feud.</b>

29
01:01:09,133 --> 01:01:10,033
<b>The conflict is an</b>

30
01:01:10,033 --> 01:01:12,033
<b>ancient, eternal holy war.</b>

31
01:01:12,699 --> 01:01:15,033
<b>The story goes that Jews and Muslims have</b>

32
01:01:15,033 --> 01:01:16,900
<b>been locked in a religious struggle over</b>

33
01:01:16,900 --> 01:01:18,333
<b>the Holy Land for centuries.</b>

34
01:01:19,133 --> 01:01:21,066
<b>It's an easy narrative because it writes</b>

35
01:01:21,066 --> 01:01:23,066
<b>the whole thing off as an inevitable</b>

36
01:01:23,066 --> 01:01:24,766
<b>clash of ancient hatreds.</b>

37
01:01:25,800 --> 01:01:27,066
<b>This is simply not true.</b>

38
01:01:27,733 --> 01:01:29,800
<b>The modern Israeli-Palestinian conflict</b>

39
01:01:29,800 --> 01:01:31,633
<b>is a product of the late</b>

40
01:01:31,633 --> 01:01:34,000
<b>19th and 20th centuries.</b>

41
01:01:35,133 --> 01:01:37,133
<b>At its heart, it's a clash between two</b>

42
01:01:37,133 --> 01:01:39,766
<b>competing nationalist movements born from</b>

43
01:01:39,766 --> 01:01:41,266
<b>the collapse of the Ottoman Empire.</b>

44
01:01:41,500 --> 01:01:44,033
<b>For centuries, under Ottoman rule, Jews,</b>

45
01:01:44,300 --> 01:01:46,433
<b>Christians and Muslims coexisted in the</b>

46
01:01:46,433 --> 01:01:48,466
<b>region with a degree of relative peace.</b>

47
01:01:48,833 --> 01:01:50,533
<b>Your identity was more local and</b>

48
01:01:50,533 --> 01:01:52,099
<b>religious than national.</b>

49
01:01:52,366 --> 01:01:54,066
<b>That all started to change with the rise</b>

50
01:01:54,066 --> 01:01:55,666
<b>of modern nationalism in Europe.</b>

51
01:01:55,966 --> 01:01:57,199
<b>Two movements emerged</b>

52
01:01:57,199 --> 01:01:58,933
<b>at roughly the same time.</b>

53
01:01:59,766 --> 01:02:01,699
<b>Zionism, which argued that the Jewish</b>

54
01:02:01,699 --> 01:02:04,000
<b>people were a nation deserving of a state</b>

55
01:02:04,000 --> 01:02:05,766
<b>in their ancestral homeland,</b>

56
01:02:06,833 --> 01:02:09,500
<b>and Arab nationalism, which sought</b>

57
01:02:09,500 --> 01:02:11,833
<b>independence from Ottoman and later</b>

58
01:02:11,833 --> 01:02:13,466
<b>European colonial rule.</b>

59
01:02:13,933 --> 01:02:16,266
<b>Palestinian nationalism then grew as its</b>

60
01:02:16,266 --> 01:02:17,666
<b>own distinct movement,</b>

61
01:02:17,966 --> 01:02:19,633
<b>partially in response to the Ottoman</b>

62
01:02:19,633 --> 01:02:22,133
<b>decline and partially in response to</b>

63
01:02:22,133 --> 01:02:23,266
<b>increasing Zionist</b>

64
01:02:23,266 --> 01:02:26,400
<b>immigration in the early 20th century.</b>

65
01:02:26,599 --> 01:02:27,933
<b>So the conflict isn't about</b>

66
01:02:27,933 --> 01:02:29,466
<b>the Quran versus the Torah.</b>

67
01:02:29,866 --> 01:02:32,766
<b>It's about land, sovereignty and</b>

68
01:02:32,766 --> 01:02:35,533
<b>self-determination between two groups who</b>

69
01:02:35,533 --> 01:02:37,166
<b>see the very same territory</b>

70
01:02:37,166 --> 01:02:38,766
<b>as their national homeland.</b>

71
01:02:38,900 --> 01:02:41,500
<b>Framing it as an ancient religious feud</b>

72
01:02:41,500 --> 01:02:44,066
<b>ignores the modern and political forces</b>

73
01:02:44,066 --> 01:02:45,733
<b>that actually lead the fuse.</b>

74
01:02:46,266 --> 01:02:48,466
<b>Myth two, the Jewish</b>

75
01:02:48,466 --> 01:02:49,633
<b>connection to the land.</b>

76
01:02:49,966 --> 01:02:52,033
<b>This claim is often used to frame the</b>

77
01:02:52,033 --> 01:02:53,766
<b>conflict in a very specific way,</b>

78
01:02:53,800 --> 01:02:56,233
<b>that Jewish people are foreign to the</b>

79
01:02:56,233 --> 01:02:58,466
<b>Middle East and have no legitimate</b>

80
01:02:58,466 --> 01:03:00,800
<b>historical tie to the land we now call</b>

81
01:03:00,800 --> 01:03:02,066
<b>Israel and Palestine.</b>

82
01:03:02,066 --> 01:03:04,433
<b>The argument basically says the Jewish</b>

83
01:03:04,433 --> 01:03:06,633
<b>connection is purely religious, not</b>

84
01:03:06,633 --> 01:03:07,766
<b>historical or ancestral.</b>

85
01:03:07,800 --> 01:03:10,666
<b>Archaeological and historical records</b>

86
01:03:10,666 --> 01:03:12,266
<b>tell a very different story.</b>

87
01:03:13,099 --> 01:03:15,133
<b>Long before the rise of Christianity or</b>

88
01:03:15,133 --> 01:03:17,699
<b>Islam, ancient Jewish kingdoms,</b>

89
01:03:18,166 --> 01:03:20,266
<b>specifically the kingdoms of Israel and</b>

90
01:03:20,266 --> 01:03:22,266
<b>Judah, were centered here.</b>

91
01:03:22,933 --> 01:03:24,533
<b>We have inscriptions from neighboring</b>

92
01:03:24,533 --> 01:03:27,033
<b>empires like Egypt and Assyria</b>

93
01:03:27,033 --> 01:03:27,766
<b>that refer to these kingdoms.</b>

94
01:03:28,800 --> 01:03:31,966
<b>The famous "Mernaptas" Tele, an Egyptian</b>

95
01:03:31,966 --> 01:03:33,833
<b>artifact from the 13th</b>

96
01:03:33,833 --> 01:03:34,766
<b>century before Christ,</b>

97
01:03:35,400 --> 01:03:38,233
<b>contains the earliest known non-biblical</b>

98
01:03:38,233 --> 01:03:40,166
<b>reference to Israel as</b>

99
01:03:40,166 --> 01:03:41,233
<b>a people in the land.</b>

100
01:03:41,733 --> 01:03:44,500
<b>Despite that and despite waves of exile,</b>

101
01:03:44,833 --> 01:03:46,833
<b>a Jewish presence has remained in the</b>

102
01:03:46,833 --> 01:03:49,466
<b>land continuously for thousands of years.</b>

103
01:03:49,900 --> 01:03:52,066
<b>Archaeologists have uncovered countless</b>

104
01:03:52,066 --> 01:03:53,766
<b>artifacts backing this up.</b>

105
01:03:53,800 --> 01:03:56,733
<b>They've found royal seals with the names</b>

106
01:03:56,733 --> 01:03:59,166
<b>of Judean kings mentioned in the Bible.</b>

107
01:04:00,266 --> 01:04:03,366
<b>An Aramaic inscription found that Teldan</b>

108
01:04:03,366 --> 01:04:06,366
<b>explicitly mentions the House of David,</b>

109
01:04:06,966 --> 01:04:09,166
<b>proving that the Davidic dynasty was</b>

110
01:04:09,166 --> 01:04:12,033
<b>recognized as a political reality by the</b>

111
01:04:12,033 --> 01:04:13,800
<b>9th century before Christ.</b>

112
01:04:14,333 --> 01:04:16,733
<b>After the Romans crushed the final Jewish</b>

113
01:04:16,733 --> 01:04:20,633
<b>revolt in 135, they renamed the province</b>

114
01:04:20,633 --> 01:04:22,766
<b>from Judea to Syria-Palestine,</b>

115
01:04:22,833 --> 01:04:25,366
<b>a move many historians believe was a</b>

116
01:04:25,366 --> 01:04:27,466
<b>deliberate attempt to erase the Jewish</b>

117
01:04:27,466 --> 01:04:28,633
<b>connection to the land.</b>

118
01:04:29,433 --> 01:04:32,233
<b>Despite that and despite waves of exile,</b>

119
01:04:32,500 --> 01:04:34,766
<b>a Jewish presence has remained in the</b>

120
01:04:34,766 --> 01:04:36,466
<b>land for thousands of years.</b>

121
01:04:36,800 --> 01:04:38,533
<b>Teldanitis' connection isn't just</b>

122
01:04:38,533 --> 01:04:40,866
<b>misreading history, it's denying</b>

123
01:04:40,866 --> 01:04:42,866
<b>mountains of historical evidence.</b>

124
01:04:43,333 --> 01:04:46,733
<b>Myth 3. Israel as a colonial project</b>

125
01:04:46,833 --> 01:04:49,966
<b>This builds on the last myth, that the</b>

126
01:04:49,966 --> 01:04:51,866
<b>state of Israel is just a European</b>

127
01:04:51,866 --> 01:04:55,033
<b>settler colonial project, with no real</b>

128
01:04:55,033 --> 01:04:56,300
<b>roots in the Middle East.</b>

129
01:04:57,366 --> 01:04:59,699
<b>This narrative paints Zionism as another</b>

130
01:04:59,699 --> 01:05:02,933
<b>branch of European colonialism and Jewish</b>

131
01:05:02,933 --> 01:05:04,833
<b>Israelis as foreign invaders.</b>

132
01:05:06,133 --> 01:05:08,599
<b>While modern political Zionism was</b>

133
01:05:08,599 --> 01:05:10,966
<b>definitely influenced by 19th century</b>

134
01:05:10,966 --> 01:05:13,133
<b>European ideas about nationalism,</b>

135
01:05:14,066 --> 01:05:16,366
<b>calling it a purely European project</b>

136
01:05:16,366 --> 01:05:18,133
<b>erases half of the story.</b>

137
01:05:18,933 --> 01:05:21,166
<b>A huge portion of Israel's Jewish</b>

138
01:05:21,166 --> 01:05:22,633
<b>population isn't of</b>

139
01:05:22,633 --> 01:05:24,066
<b>European descent at all.</b>

140
01:05:24,966 --> 01:05:27,400
<b>They are the Mizrahi and Sephardic Jews,</b>

141
01:05:27,966 --> 01:05:29,866
<b>the descendants of Jewish communities</b>

142
01:05:29,866 --> 01:05:31,400
<b>that had lived for centuries,</b>

143
01:05:32,099 --> 01:05:33,733
<b>sometimes millennia, in the</b>

144
01:05:33,733 --> 01:05:34,900
<b>Middle East and North Africa.</b>

145
01:05:35,833 --> 01:05:39,333
<b>After Israel's creation in 1948, waves of</b>

146
01:05:39,333 --> 01:05:41,933
<b>state sanctioned persecution and violence</b>

147
01:05:41,933 --> 01:05:43,866
<b>were unleashed against Jewish</b>

148
01:05:43,866 --> 01:05:45,733
<b>populations in Arab countries.</b>

149
01:05:46,333 --> 01:05:48,166
<b>Fearing for their lives an estimated</b>

150
01:05:48,166 --> 01:05:52,699
<b>850,000 Mizrahi and Sephardic Jews were</b>

151
01:05:52,699 --> 01:05:55,066
<b>either expelled or fled from countries</b>

152
01:05:55,066 --> 01:05:57,766
<b>like Iraq, Egypt, Yemen and Morocco.</b>

153
01:05:57,800 --> 01:06:02,233
<b>Between 1948 and the early 1970s, nearly</b>

154
01:06:02,233 --> 01:06:03,833
<b>600,000 of these</b>

155
01:06:03,833 --> 01:06:05,633
<b>refugees poured into Israel.</b>

156
01:06:06,066 --> 01:06:08,766
<b>These were not European colonizers, they</b>

157
01:06:08,766 --> 01:06:09,699
<b>were Middle Eastern</b>

158
01:06:09,699 --> 01:06:11,233
<b>and North African people.</b>

159
01:06:11,566 --> 01:06:14,166
<b>Today, they and their descendants make up</b>

160
01:06:14,166 --> 01:06:16,233
<b>roughly half of Israel's population.</b>

161
01:06:17,000 --> 01:06:19,233
<b>Their story complicates the whole</b>

162
01:06:19,233 --> 01:06:22,466
<b>European project narrative, revealing a</b>

163
01:06:22,466 --> 01:06:23,766
<b>more complex picture.</b>

164
01:06:23,800 --> 01:06:27,500
<b>The gathering of a global diaspora with</b>

165
01:06:27,500 --> 01:06:29,699
<b>deep indigenous roots in the Middle East</b>

166
01:06:29,699 --> 01:06:32,333
<b>finally back in their ancestral homeland.</b>

167
01:06:32,699 --> 01:06:36,099
<b>Myth 4. The idea of Palestine.</b>

168
01:06:36,433 --> 01:06:37,966
<b>Another pervasive myth</b>

169
01:06:37,966 --> 01:06:40,000
<b>revolves around the name Palestine.</b>

170
01:06:40,633 --> 01:06:43,000
<b>The claim goes that Palestine has always</b>

171
01:06:43,000 --> 01:06:46,133
<b>been a distinct Arab country and that the</b>

172
01:06:46,133 --> 01:06:48,233
<b>term "Palestinian" has always referred</b>

173
01:06:48,233 --> 01:06:49,533
<b>only to its Arab inhabitants.</b>

174
01:06:50,566 --> 01:06:53,800
<b>This suggests there was a continuous Arab</b>

175
01:06:53,800 --> 01:06:55,199
<b>nation that was just</b>

176
01:06:55,199 --> 01:06:56,566
<b>interrupted by Zionism.</b>

177
01:06:57,333 --> 01:06:58,833
<b>Historically, that's not quite right.</b>

178
01:06:59,199 --> 01:06:59,966
<b>The name Palestine</b>

179
01:06:59,966 --> 01:07:01,500
<b>isn't even Arab in origin.</b>

180
01:07:01,966 --> 01:07:03,500
<b>The Roman Empire imposed</b>

181
01:07:03,500 --> 01:07:05,533
<b>it on the region around 135.</b>

182
01:07:06,199 --> 01:07:08,800
<b>As mentioned, this was after they crushed</b>

183
01:07:08,800 --> 01:07:11,866
<b>a Jewish revolt and it was a way to sever</b>

184
01:07:11,866 --> 01:07:14,233
<b>the land's Jewish connection by naming it</b>

185
01:07:14,233 --> 01:07:16,033
<b>after the Philistines, an</b>

186
01:07:16,033 --> 01:07:17,533
<b>ancient enemy of the Israelites.</b>

187
01:07:17,599 --> 01:07:21,666
<b>For the next 1800 years, Palestine was</b>

188
01:07:21,666 --> 01:07:23,833
<b>just a name for a region, not an</b>

189
01:07:23,833 --> 01:07:25,000
<b>independent country.</b>

190
01:07:25,833 --> 01:07:27,833
<b>It was controlled by a series of empires.</b>

191
01:07:28,599 --> 01:07:32,333
<b>The Romans, Byzantines, various Islamic</b>

192
01:07:32,333 --> 01:07:34,033
<b>caliphates, crusaders</b>

193
01:07:34,033 --> 01:07:35,599
<b>and finally the Ottomans.</b>

194
01:07:36,433 --> 01:07:38,533
<b>During this time, a Palestinian was</b>

195
01:07:38,533 --> 01:07:40,300
<b>simply anyone who lived there.</b>

196
01:07:40,599 --> 01:07:42,766
<b>A Jew, Christian, Muslim.</b>

197
01:07:43,133 --> 01:07:45,500
<b>In fact, until the mid-20th century,</b>

198
01:07:45,833 --> 01:07:46,633
<b>Zionist organizations</b>

199
01:07:46,633 --> 01:07:48,500
<b>used the term frequently.</b>

200
01:07:49,000 --> 01:07:51,033
<b>The newspaper we know today as the</b>

201
01:07:51,033 --> 01:07:53,833
<b>Jerusalem Post was founded by a Jew in</b>

202
01:07:53,833 --> 01:07:56,199
<b>1932 as the Palestine Post.</b>

203
01:07:56,766 --> 01:07:59,133
<b>The Palestine Symphony Orchestra, founded</b>

204
01:07:59,133 --> 01:08:02,500
<b>in 1936 to save Jewish musicians from</b>

205
01:08:02,500 --> 01:08:03,633
<b>persecution in Europe,</b>

206
01:08:03,633 --> 01:08:05,199
<b>was a Jewish orchestra.</b>

207
01:08:06,199 --> 01:08:08,633
<b>The exclusive identification of the term</b>

208
01:08:08,633 --> 01:08:12,533
<b>Palestinian with the Arab population is a</b>

209
01:08:12,533 --> 01:08:14,000
<b>much more recent development.</b>

210
01:08:14,533 --> 01:08:16,699
<b>It solidified as a distinct nationalistic</b>

211
01:08:16,699 --> 01:08:19,633
<b>identity in the 20th century, especially</b>

212
01:08:19,633 --> 01:08:21,433
<b>after the Palestinian liberation</b>

213
01:08:21,433 --> 01:08:24,300
<b>organization was formed in 1964.</b>

214
01:08:25,533 --> 01:08:27,199
<b>This doesn't take away from the modern</b>

215
01:08:27,199 --> 01:08:29,100
<b>Palestinian identity or their</b>

216
01:08:29,100 --> 01:08:30,100
<b>nationalistic aspirations.</b>

217
01:08:31,566 --> 01:08:33,899
<b>But it does make it clear that the idea</b>

218
01:08:33,899 --> 01:08:36,766
<b>of an exclusively Arab nation state</b>

219
01:08:36,766 --> 01:08:39,199
<b>called Palestine existing for centuries</b>

220
01:08:39,199 --> 01:08:41,833
<b>just isn't historically accurate.</b>

221
01:08:42,633 --> 01:08:45,699
<b>Myth 5. The Claim of Genocide</b>

222
01:08:45,699 --> 01:08:48,366
<b>Finally, we have to address the most</b>

223
01:08:48,366 --> 01:08:50,766
<b>serious and inflammatory claim of all,</b>

224
01:08:51,066 --> 01:08:53,333
<b>that Israel is committing genocide</b>

225
01:08:53,333 --> 01:08:54,533
<b>against the Palestinian people.</b>

226
01:08:55,566 --> 01:08:57,500
<b>This accusation is no longer on the</b>

227
01:08:57,500 --> 01:08:59,399
<b>fringes, it's part of mainstream</b>

228
01:08:59,399 --> 01:09:01,199
<b>discourse and legal challenges.</b>

229
01:09:02,266 --> 01:09:04,433
<b>The word genocide has a very specific</b>

230
01:09:04,433 --> 01:09:06,133
<b>legal definition under the</b>

231
01:09:06,133 --> 01:09:08,333
<b>1948 Genocide Convention.</b>

232
01:09:09,233 --> 01:09:11,633
<b>To prove it, you have to show an intent</b>

233
01:09:11,633 --> 01:09:14,433
<b>to destroy, in whole or in part, a</b>

234
01:09:14,433 --> 01:09:15,800
<b>national, ethnical,</b>

235
01:09:16,100 --> 01:09:17,533
<b>racial or religious group.</b>

236
01:09:18,100 --> 01:09:19,899
<b>While the conflict has caused immense</b>

237
01:09:19,899 --> 01:09:22,333
<b>suffering, death and displacement for</b>

238
01:09:22,333 --> 01:09:24,600
<b>Palestinians, the legal question is</b>

239
01:09:24,600 --> 01:09:26,100
<b>whether it meets that</b>

240
01:09:26,100 --> 01:09:27,233
<b>incredibly high bar.</b>

241
01:09:27,800 --> 01:09:30,666
<b>Those who argue that it is genocide point</b>

242
01:09:30,666 --> 01:09:32,699
<b>to the high civilian death toll in</b>

243
01:09:32,699 --> 01:09:35,199
<b>Israeli military operations, the blockade</b>

244
01:09:35,199 --> 01:09:38,133
<b>of Gaza and inflammatory statements by</b>

245
01:09:38,133 --> 01:09:39,533
<b>some Israeli officials</b>

246
01:09:39,533 --> 01:09:41,533
<b>as evidence of intent.</b>

247
01:09:41,566 --> 01:09:44,133
<b>However, other analysts and legal</b>

248
01:09:44,133 --> 01:09:46,533
<b>scholars point to crucial evidence that</b>

249
01:09:46,533 --> 01:09:47,699
<b>contradicts the claim.</b>

250
01:09:48,733 --> 01:09:50,433
<b>Critically, the Palestinian population</b>

251
01:09:50,433 --> 01:09:51,800
<b>has grown dramatically.</b>

252
01:09:52,600 --> 01:09:55,466
<b>In 1948, the Palestinian population</b>

253
01:09:55,466 --> 01:09:57,399
<b>worldwide was estimated</b>

254
01:09:57,399 --> 01:09:59,100
<b>at around 1.4 million.</b>

255
01:09:59,766 --> 01:10:03,000
<b>By 2023, estimates put that number at</b>

256
01:10:03,000 --> 01:10:06,533
<b>over 14.6 million, a tenfold increase.</b>

257
01:10:07,566 --> 01:10:10,300
<b>That demographic reality runs contrary to</b>

258
01:10:10,300 --> 01:10:12,833
<b>the intent to destroy a population, which</b>

259
01:10:12,833 --> 01:10:14,333
<b>is the core of the legal</b>

260
01:10:14,333 --> 01:10:15,600
<b>definition of genocide.</b>

261
01:10:16,433 --> 01:10:18,000
<b>Israel maintains that its military</b>

262
01:10:18,000 --> 01:10:19,733
<b>actions are aimed at Hamas,</b>

263
01:10:19,800 --> 01:10:21,133
<b>not the Palestinian people.</b>

264
01:10:21,899 --> 01:10:23,766
<b>Even with the devastating and tragic</b>

265
01:10:23,766 --> 01:10:26,066
<b>civilian casualties that occur, the</b>

266
01:10:26,066 --> 01:10:27,800
<b>debate over whether these actions</b>

267
01:10:27,800 --> 01:10:29,733
<b>constitute war crimes is a</b>

268
01:10:29,733 --> 01:10:31,633
<b>valid and necessary question.</b>

269
01:10:31,666 --> 01:10:35,166
<b>But as for genocide, the legal question</b>

270
01:10:35,166 --> 01:10:36,933
<b>is still very much contested.</b>

271
01:10:37,100 --> 01:10:40,166
<b>While many legal experts agree that the</b>

272
01:10:40,166 --> 01:10:42,833
<b>high bar of intent to destroy has not</b>

273
01:10:42,833 --> 01:10:45,399
<b>been met, the issue is being actively</b>

274
01:10:45,399 --> 01:10:49,166
<b>debated in international forums in 2025,</b>

275
01:10:49,699 --> 01:10:51,466
<b>and no international court has given a</b>

276
01:10:51,466 --> 01:10:52,633
<b>definitive ruling yet.</b>

277
01:10:53,666 --> 01:10:55,833
<b>Look, digging into these myths isn't</b>

278
01:10:55,833 --> 01:10:58,100
<b>about picking a side, or saying one</b>

279
01:10:58,100 --> 01:10:59,100
<b>group's suffering</b>

280
01:10:59,100 --> 01:11:00,899
<b>matters less than another's.</b>

281
01:11:00,899 --> 01:11:02,333
<b>It's about clearing the fog.</b>

282
01:11:02,699 --> 01:11:03,933
<b>These narratives aren't</b>

283
01:11:03,933 --> 01:11:05,199
<b>just historical mistakes.</b>

284
01:11:05,699 --> 01:11:08,133
<b>They are weapons in an information war</b>

285
01:11:08,133 --> 01:11:10,833
<b>that make a very complex reality nearly</b>

286
01:11:10,833 --> 01:11:12,333
<b>impossible to grasp.</b>

287
01:11:13,100 --> 01:11:14,733
<b>They can turn a modern nationalist</b>

288
01:11:14,733 --> 01:11:17,500
<b>conflict into an eternal religious war.</b>

289
01:11:17,899 --> 01:11:20,233
<b>They can erase one people's history while</b>

290
01:11:20,233 --> 01:11:21,633
<b>misrepresenting another's.</b>

291
01:11:22,666 --> 01:11:24,233
<b>And they can deploy one of the most</b>

292
01:11:24,233 --> 01:11:27,666
<b>severe accusations without meeting the</b>

293
01:11:27,666 --> 01:11:29,500
<b>rigorous threshold for evidence.</b>

294
01:11:30,266 --> 01:11:32,199
<b>A more informed conversation doesn't</b>

295
01:11:32,199 --> 01:11:34,100
<b>start with more anger,</b>

296
01:11:34,600 --> 01:11:35,866
<b>but with more accuracy.</b>

297
01:11:36,399 --> 01:11:38,600
<b>It begins by setting aside the convenient</b>

298
01:11:38,600 --> 01:11:40,399
<b>myths and confronting the</b>

299
01:11:40,399 --> 01:11:42,466
<b>messy, complex historical record.</b>

300
01:11:42,833 --> 01:11:45,433
<b>The truth is rarely as simple as the</b>

301
01:11:45,433 --> 01:11:46,633
<b>stories that we are told.</b>

302
01:11:47,033 --> 01:11:48,866
<b>If you value these kinds of historical</b>

303
01:11:48,866 --> 01:11:51,100
<b>deep dives, be sure to subscribe.</b>

304
01:11:51,699 --> 01:11:53,133
<b>And please share your</b>

305
01:11:53,133 --> 01:11:54,399
<b>thoughts in the comments below.</b>

306
01:11:54,566 --> 01:11:56,033
<b>Thank you for listening.</b>

